As with all my remixes, I had to wait on some equipment before I could record the guitar parts properly and that left me no time to master it all properly. There shall be a remaster soon. author: Riot Act
title: A Blissful State of Ignorance
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2515 - Zero-Sum, A Blissful State of Ignorance, by Riot Act.mp3
author_blurb:
January 2009

I started this about a week ago...  Got better as it went :)

The whole thing was crafted in FLStudio 8.  I fed the original drum track through a gate and delay, similar to what I did with Vessel, then fed that through effect 76 on the new toy (GO MINI-KP!).

Everything else is pretty simple.  I spent a good 5 or 6 hours on this tweaking and mixing... I hope you like it :)

Take care guys, I hope the holidays were good!

author: Gary Lester
title: Frantic
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2761 - Only, Frantic, by Gary Lester.mp3
author_blurb:
If anybody cares here is a little info on what drives me in making a particular remix composition.
Things start to happen when I begin with an open mind, usually spontaneously.
I have a system believe it or not!
What I do is load the original track and then switch off every instrument. Then I turn on one instrument or vocal track and find the sound that has prompted my curiosity.
Once a specific sound has been isolated and moved towards the front I then start searching specifically for complimentary sounds.
From there it starts to flow.
I make comparisons by turning on additional sounds or adding instruments till I reach a beat and sound that drives me to stick with it.
At that point I replay the song several times making adjustments to noise level, timing and details like which speaker is better for a particular tracks playback. 
The musicality of Trent Reznor(TR) and Nine Inch Nails(NIN) is still amazing to me! 
I am still extremely appreciative of TR, NIN and those who operate this site.
Good luck!

author: Rob'd
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2773 - Survivalism remixed by Rob'd.mp3
author_blurb: I always thought the drum track of the original Survivalism song was so lacking, it really bothered me.  My goal in this remix was to add a more driving drum track.  The drum track is all midi, done in GarageBand.  I worked hard on it, and I still think it is far from perfect.  I also added a bit of my own spice in little fuzzy guitar solos, drum solos and a piano solo.  I hope you like it!

author: DJ Poly
title: Thank God For Given' Us Trent
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2791 - God Given, Thank God For Given' Us Trent, by DJ Poly.mp3
tags: Something I Can Never Ha, Terrible Lie, smart
fulltags: Something I Can Never Ha, smart, Terrible Lie, The Great Below, Vessel, The Hand That Feeds, Ringfinger, mashup, fresh. mashup, cool, god given, Head Like a Hole, Into The Void, Heresy, Closer
author_blurb:
Somewhere between a remix and a mashup. I used GG's sourse files and a bunch of other NIN tracks in their original complete-mixed form (a lot of pitchshifting and time stretching - so it is a bit messy at some points). 

tracks included in the mix: Head Like a Hole, Terrible Lie, Something I Can Never Have, Ringfinger, Vessel, Heresy, Closer, The Hand That Feeds, Into The Void, The Great Below

Enjoy!

BTW, check out another great work:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hT5eJwgAtvY

author: Myotherme
title: Desperate Mix
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2762 - Me, I'm Not, Desperate Mix, by Myotherme.mp3
author_blurb:
Made using FL7.

I've been learning FL for about 6 months now using the "tweak and see what happens" method of learning because I am too lazy to read articles on what you're supposed to do (and my way is more fun).

This track is a song that I've been writing for a couple of days, threw the lyrics for Me, I'm Not over the top for a laugh, tweaked bits here and there to fit and it's turned out one of the few things I've written that I'm quite proud of. Well, for now!

Although, having said that, the mixing probably sounds like shit cos 1) I don't have wicked cool speakers and 2) I don't know what I'm doing.

Enjoy!

author: DeeJay Gamer
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2853 - Capital G remixed by DeeJay Gamer.mp3
author_blurb:
The mix is kind of tentative right now, I might make changes to it, such as one part I'm not sure about but put some work into is the "wind stick" part after the first chorus. It's inspired by an instrument used by the Blue Man Group and it's a tube I got a glow stick out of and I'm waving it around to create the sound. Unfortunately, it would only record on my digital camera, my actual microphone could barely pick up the sound at all.
The new loop samples come from a free music loop website, the terms of service gave no conditions for use, but I think it's safe to assume that non-profit use is okay.  There's a slightly higher-quality version of this song on my MySpace page:
http://www.myspace.com/deejaygamer
Along with a cover of "Gave Up".

author: George L
title: My Place in Everything
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2930 - Vessel, My Place in Everything, by George L.mp3
author_blurb:
Hi, 
this is my first remix.
Tell me what you think.

I tried to do something different while maintaining some of the original song's appeal.
I also structured the music so that it alternates between heavy and melodic, while building up in the end. I had to compress the WAV file into mp3 so I'm not sure how the quality will turn out during the loud parts, but overall it sounds good. There are a lot of layers and texture sounds, so listen carefully,and u could hear some cool sounds, especially during the chorus ad the end. I hope this remix kicks some ass, and if you like it, let me know, I'll make some mo' 
Thanks for listenting.

Peace gangstas

-George

author: Bryce Miller [G[M]X]
title: The End
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 2997 - Survivalism, The End, by Bryce Miller [G[M]X].mp3
author_blurb:
My first remix. Uses samples from Orson Welles' "War of the Worlds", which, according to this website (http://www.war-of-the-worlds.org/Radio/):

"War of the Worlds and related imagery are Copyright by Paramount.
Defend Fair Use 	

You may copy, distribute, prepare derivative works, reproduce, introduce into an electronic retrieval system, perform, and transmit portions of this publication provided that such use constitutes "fair use" under copyright law, or is otherwise permitted by applicable law."

Regardless, I struggled a lot, but it was a lot of fun and I learned quite a bit. I'm still not sure if the drums at the beginning are at the right volume, so feel free to input.

author: Theday
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3072 - The Beginning of the End remixed by Theday.mp3
author_blurb:
http://schmilar.blogspot.com

I'd like to thanks Trent Reznor and company for releasing the audio files and creating such a fun experiment. I'd also like to thanks the NINRemixes.com community for listening and rating my work. Thanks, keep it up!

Anyway, I was confused about this song. I thought,' How do you improve on perfection?!' After playing around for a bit I found a way. Remember to listen to the entire song before rating.

author: Tiffany Shea
title: Drifting
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3073 - Only, Drifting, by Tiffany Shea.mp3
author_blurb: i am a songwriter/touring musician by trade having recorded 12 of my own albums; but this was my very first time to experiment with remixing. it actually started as something just to get myself more familiar with pro-tools when my friend told me about the downloadable individual tracks... but once i started doing it, it totally just took over my artist self and ended up being just as fun as writing my own music (www.tiffanyshea.com, www.myspace.com/tiffanysheaband). also, type in "tiffany shea hurt" into youtube to see a live performace of me doin NIN "Hurt"... you'll dig it.

author: Bill Kates
title: Old Ego Sex Narcissus
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3165 - Only, Old Ego Sex Narcissus, by Bill Kates.mp3
fulltags: old ego, narcissus, Only, weird, What you see, Moody, Manson, bonzo, funny, glass, gonzo, Blues
author_blurb:
I submit this as something not to be taken seriously or sold, but merely the results of experimenting with a serious sense of fun and humor on and off for about two years, with the fantastic source material so generously supplied by Mr. Reznor. I can't explain or exclaim my joy adequately at how very much I feel I learned kust respectfully fooling around with these tracks in ProTools. Thanks, Trent, if I can convey that to you somehow, sir. 
This "musique concret" contains samples from several random sources, along with my own and Geneveive Yang's vocals. Ummm... if anyone is about to get sued or something if this is distributed, then please don't distribute it. I would be honored with any and all critiques.

author: Stephan Carroll
title: Beyond This Twilight
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3213 - In This Twilight, Beyond This Twilight, by Stephan Carroll.mp3
author_blurb:
To be honest, I was never a big fan of NIN until Year Zero. Sure, I had listened to some of the albums, but Year Zero and the whole alternate reality websites campaign really drew me in. Specifically, In This Twilight struck a nerve deep within me and led me to compose an entire orchestral and choral suite about the final normal day on earth (loosely patterned after Gustov Holsts Planets suite). Its just been released on my website: 

www.stephancarroll.com 

Now that the album is complete, I decided to do a huge orchestral/choral arrangement of In This Twilight. Hope you enjoy!

author: theMUTE
title: Me, I'm Ghost
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3253 - Me, I'm Not, Me, I'm Ghost, by theMUTE.mp3
author_blurb: The source files for 'Year Zero' being easily available, I thought a nice idea would be adding elements from the previous NIN release to the newest one. This is the first remix of this sort I've tried so far. I've added vocal and bass tracks from "Me, I'm Not" to the "Ghosts 35" track. A quick and fun remix, I enjoyed the results and look forward to more experimentation with these albums.

author: Swatsinger
title: FlySwatting Mix
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3255 - Capital G, FlySwatting Mix, by Swatsinger.mp3
author_blurb: I grabbed a few public domain audio samples of political speeches and a few police radio pieces to work with the samples near the end. This entire thing was wholly improvisational -- I really wanted something that was Nurse with Wound twitchy, something that didn't have much foundation. I deleted a few audio tracks and put in my own MIDI tracks that I'd written, then put it all together. I actually like it, which is rare for things I've created, seeing as I really criticize myself far too much.

author: DJB
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3284 - The Hand That Feeds remixed by DJB.mp3
author_blurb:
I originally did this as a GarageBand demo. I started this on a G3 iMac, but as the file grew and grew (and GREW) I moved it to a G5 to finish. My nitpicking took 4 months to complete. 
This is more like a "correction" than a remix, dragging the song kicking and screaming back to it's old-school, Chicago-style industrial roots, if that makes sense. It kicks ass. Really.

title: 13th Hour v1.0
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3356 - Zero-Sum, 13th Hour v1.0, by Halo_D9.mp3
author_blurb:
Zero-Sum (Year Zero), remixed with samples from the J-RPG hit video game, "Shin Megami Tensei: Persona 3".

If you've played or beaten the game, then you know that the lyrics to Zero-Sum somewhat explain the game's entire plot (and or true meaning), as evidenced here.

Thus, why I made this mix.

If not (you didn't realize the link between the two), you may just now realize something beautifully transmorgrified into a mashup of uber-awesomeness.

If this mix is accepted...
Enjoy. ;)

author: Knqulear Shift
title: Letting You Self Destruct
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3408 - Letting You, Letting You Self Destruct, by Knqulear Shift.mp3
author_blurb:
Looking thru some older stuff I came across some midi files of Mr.Self Destruct. Loaded em up into Logic and did a bit of work by switching the midi files to new tracks then assigning them each to Absynth and drum machines trying to find the right sound for the mix. Then speed the tempo down, added Trent screaming the Letting You vocals, added a few small electro drum loops, some live drum loops, and some extra synth.
Thought it would be a fun project, it was but it really was not an easy one, although it was good practice for future stuff.

Would like to work on project(s) with others, via over the net.
You can give me a shout, or leave a comment on a song I'll find it, I check comments and the shoutbox quite often.

K.S.

author: Halo_D9
title: 13th Hour v2.0
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3454 - Zero-Sum, 13th Hour v2.0, by Halo_D9.mp3
author_blurb:
Version 2.0 of my "13th Hour" remix of Zero-Sum. My other one (V1.0) was submitted under my real name, "Ryan". This (Halo_D9) is my official remix.nin.com username. If you wish to clarify this, email me at the given email on the official account profile.

Anyways, again I must note that this mix uses samples from the video-game "Persona 3" by ATLUS.
Used were the tracks "Aria of The Soul", "Battle Hymn of The Soul", and "Memories of The City".

I personally own the game's soundtrack.
It came with the original game (not FES) itself.

Also used, were various quotes from the game's final boss Nyx Avatar. Which reflect on the given lyrics of Zero-Sum after each quote.

The overall meaning/plot of P3 is summed up here, within the lyrics of this Zero-Sum remix. Which is why I made this mixmash to begin with. To express the similarities between ZS and P3.

Anyways, to note the differences:

(Between v1.0 and v2.0)

Along with the Nyx Avatar quotes and added tune from the OST (Memories of The City), new beats were added in from Zero-Sum as well in a few new spots during the end. Along with the piano outro as well. Which again, appears at the end.

Enjoy! ^^

author: Pete Gerr
title: Maybe I Am v5
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3458 - Me, I'm Not, Maybe I Am v5, by Pete Gerr.mp3
author_blurb: The basic beat foundation to Me I'm Not hooked me the very first time I heard it, and I've been working with the basic structure for some time in just an instrumental remix form. The basic beat foundation, I think, is so strong and universally interesting, that in this version, I've experimented by adding, among other things an Indian percussion instrument sample and a fairly classic broken beat rock drum as a subtle shift - I think they fit pretty well, a testament to the original. The song is really long, just over 8:00, so I've had to encode it at 96kbps, lower than I would have liked.

author: Halo_D9
title: Twilight V2.0
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3550 - Lights in the Sky, Twilight V2.0, by Halo_D9.mp3
author_blurb:
Sources used include (not in any order):

-Lights In The Sky (The Slip)
-In This Twilight (Year Zero)
-HYPERPOWER! (Year Zero)
-The Downward Spiral [The Bottom] (Further Down The Spiral)
-Twist (Ringfinger Demo) (Pretty Hate Machine Demos)
-999,999 (The Slip)

I am uploading this here, cuz the official remix site is acting up and not letting me upload anything at all. So when that problem is rectified, expect to see this there too, under a different title (Lights In The Twilight Sky).

At any rate, this is V2 of my aforementioned LITTS remix. To anyone whom has heard the original, this version adds subtle changes, introing the track, and giving it light (but well implemented) add-ins when needed.

To anyone who hasn't heard it,
uhm...enjoy?!

title: Arcade House Remix
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3554 - Survivalism, Arcade House Remix, by Arcade Velocity.mp3
author_blurb:
When the multitracks for Survivalism surfaced I churned out this catchy and hard hitting electro/disco remix and I'm still quite pleased with it. It's in my opinion my strongest NIN remix so far, better than the bite the arcade-one which took me to the ninth spot in the unoffical remix competition.

Could've been produced a bit better but I don't feel like correcting that now. This remix still sounds fresh and I hope you agree!

author: Riot Act
title: Falling on Deaf Ears
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3583 - Me, I'm Not, Falling on Deaf Ears, by Riot Act.mp3
author_blurb:
This is remix #5.

Using Trent's samples to maintain the atmosphere of the song, especially around the finale, I built this remix from the ground up in FLStudio 8.

I really hope you guys enjoy it, it's definitely a different take on the song.  

Leave me a little bit of feedback if you can, so that I can continue to learn and make the next one better.

Thanks to everyone for all the support!

author: Riot Act
title: Sparked (Remastered)
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3587 - 1,000,000, Sparked (Remastered), by Riot Act.mp3
author_blurb:
EDIT:  THIS IS A REMASTERED VERSION.

I used Adobe Audition to take some of the bite out of my original.  Hope you like this one better now that it's not blasting out your ears... or maybe that's what you wanted all along? ;)


The fourth remix.

I tried to clean up the song a little. I replaced the original drum track with a techno beat; the bass line and organ tracks are also new, and the vocals are remastered and slightly restructured.

I hope you enjoy, and as always, please please leave some feedback; the criticism goes a long way and I appreciate it.

Take care guys!

author: Riot Act
title: Jigsaw
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3617 - Lights in the Sky, Jigsaw, by Riot Act.mp3
author_blurb:
Remix #7

I created and sequenced the bed for this one from the ground up in FLStudio 8 (no stock loops!!), then reversed and modified the original ambience and used it to maintain the LITS atmosphere.

I've listened on a few sets of speakers as well as my headphones; sometimes the end vocals seem drowned out and sometimes they don't.  

Unfortunately, I didn't save my project file after doing some mixing in Audition, so any work I do on the vocals at this point may end up changing the song too much, as well as taking up a lot of time, which I haven't had a lot of lately.

Otherwise, I'm finally happy enough with this remix to post it -- I hope the tedious amounts of time I spent on it shine through to your ears :)

Enjoy.

author: Riot Act
title: Rethought
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3651 - Echoplex, Rethought, by Riot Act.mp3
author_blurb:
Remix #... 8?

(Created in FLStudio 8, remastered in Adobe Audition)

This one marks a couple creative breakthroughs for me, and I'd love some feedback on it.  First off, it's the first one with a modified bpm (124 slowed to 106).  

Second, it's the first remix that doesn't contain any of the original samples, other than the Lead Vx, which I'm kind of excited about.  I might go back through and add the background vocals, but I'm pretty sure it'd end up too busy.

I'm really concerned about the mastering job though... I think it might come across too loud.  Please let me know how it sounds for you guys -- I want to develop an ear for good general mastering.

I had a lot of fun distorting/destroying drumkits to make this, and I hope you guys enjoy it.

author: Riot Act
title: ph02_573P)-(
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3674 - Letting You, ph02_573P)-(, by Riot Act.mp3
author_blurb:
I had today off work, and not a whole lot to do.  

Remix #9

Created with a bit of synth from the original in a demo version of FLStudio 8, lol.  So much for my project file.  The bed was inspired by a song I wrote back in the day for my lovely girlfriend, so I'm dedicating this remix to her.

The songwriting and execution in the vocals of The Slip is brilliant, but I found the first half of the album a little too noisy for my liking.  

I tried to pull some of the noise out of 1,000,000, and I'm trying to do this again with Letting You.  A little feedback and criticism would be fantastic if anyone is so inclined.

Enjoy :)

author: Gary Lester
title: You Can Not Stop Us All
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3695 - My Violent Heart, You Can Not Stop Us All, by Gary Lester.mp3
author_blurb:
I was trying to improve upon a remix I had done last year by creating a new GB project and adding some guitars and drums. 
Ended up moving the two duplicate main tracks back and out of alignment. It sounded kool so I left it. On the way back through making adjustments I decided I needed one more instrument to support the volume in places. I dropped in a synth loop I had made and ended up with this final.  Something about the combo made the chorus which is quite unlike what the the instrument sounds like by itself.
Not the first time unusual things have happened when the TR vocals are involved.
Good luck!

author: Rezon8
title: Gospel of Trent
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3631 - The Warning, Gospel of Trent, by Rezon8.mp3
author_blurb:
Hey there, hope all is well on your side of the world : )

I decided to compose this remix after being inspired by Trent's performance at the recent Sacramento show. 

This has always been one of my favorite songs from Year Zero and I really enjoyed the entire process.

This is the first remix I've ever done and I look forward to sharing more in the near future. As for now, I need to finish work on my debut album and will get back to the remixes later. 

Enjoy!

Peace.

author: Riot Act
title: Torpedo in the Water
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3746 - The Warning, Torpedo in the Water, by Riot Act.mp3
author_blurb:
January 2009

I wasn't going to submit this one because when I threw it together a couple months ago I didn't really think it was good enough... but it's grown on me a little so I figured I'd put it up.  

It's fairly minimal, just the main vocal track and a couple guitars, plus some gated drums as well as my work which was created and sequenced in FLStudio 8.  

It's a little shrill, I wasn't using the most flattering equipment when I made it.  I hope you guys like it anyways.  :)

Enjoy and take care... thanks for listening.

title: Further Apart
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3761 - Echoplex, Further Apart, by Impact Carrier (Feat. Grim Trigger).mp3
author_blurb:
This is a remix of a remix. Grim Trigger Was nice enough to Release his multitracks for all of his remixes of NIN songs. (http://www.grimtrigger.com/blog/)
And as far as I know, I was the first to get to them. So thank you Grim.

I have some problems with the Outro Vox, but other than that I like it quite a bit. The only really original part to this is my Guitars and the way it was mixed. So the Artist should really be Grim Trigger (Feat. Impact Carrier), but if i posted under that it would probably be forgery.

Anyway, Here's what i made and i hope you enjoy this.

title: The Hurt Myself Mix
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3803 - Only, The Hurt Myself Mix, by Matt.mp3
author_blurb: This is my first remix that I have done using a trial version of Sony Acid Pro 7. It was a lot of work figuring out the program and effects and so forth. I've listened to a lot of the other remixes of Only on the site and I admit they are far superior. I'm happy with what I did, please leave any constructive feedback as I would like to try my hand at remixing another NIN song. Any tips/where I can read up on making a better remix so I can do better on the next one would be great. Hope you like my mix.

author: Tobias Jone
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3975 - The Greater Good remixed by Tobias Jone.mp3
author_blurb: I created this remix to enhance the track and add a little more dimension and texture to the sound whilst keeping the balance and original vision of the mix intact. Deeper, extended lows, more front to back depth and a more open, detailed soundstage is what this remix is about. Enjoy!  rnrnNB - This version is about as loud as the original cd master but I will be uploading a more dynamic "K-14" version for those who don't mind turning up the volume :)

author: Tobias Jone
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 3980 - Only remixed by Tobias Jone.mp3
author_blurb:
Hello,  
Again, this remix is the same as the original arrangement, but with a more open, less veiled sound. I've tried to concentrate on and encapsulate the inner details and nuances within the mix, together with a deeper, more articulated stereo image. This remix is about as loud as the original.

Here is a link to a 96/24 master for other NIN fans, captured directly from 1/4", with no destructive digital processing or AD clipping, but people seem  to like loud so....

http://soundcloud.com/tobiasjone/nine-inch-nails-only-tobias-jone-24-96-master

author: Carl Gwynne (Gifty Jones)
title: Zeros And Ones (Nine Inch Nails - Zero Sum Remix)
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 4106 - Zero-Sum, Zeros And Ones (Nine Inch Nails - Zero Sum Remix), by Carl Gwynne (Gifty Jones).mp3
author_blurb:
This is a remix featuring the vocals and samples of Zero Sum. It's my first proper go at making a remix for a full song, rather than incorporating another song's vocals. Have a listen and let me know what you think, especially if you think I've ruined the song for you :)

Forever thanks to Trent Reznor a.k.a Nine Inch Nails (and the background crew) for making his work available for others to learn and explore with.

The multitracks, all of N.I.N source material and samples relating to the original recording of Zero Sum I downloaded from the Nine Inch Nails website. Everything else is me :D

I started yesterday morning (9:30AM 3rd Dec) and have been working on it non-stop until this evening (5pm 4th Dec), I never regard anything as 'finished' but I'm happy to release it. Thanks again for giving me a good starting point, Trent!

author: Jeremy
title: Broken Glass Mix
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 4136 - The Hand That Feeds, Broken Glass Mix, by Jeremy.mp3
author_blurb:
This is my first hand at a remix. I've always wanted to experiment with THTF but I figured it's been done to death. Apple updated GarageBand a few months ago providing a lot more toys to play with so I thought I'd give it a try. 

About the mix: I raised the guitars, bass and vocals. Added some ambient industrial loops, clean kick, clean guitar sounds at intro and outdo and crushed everything else in the mid range... When I was a kid I'd attend church services where the preacher would often yell into the microphone too and pump his voice out into a small building at ridiculously high levels. I was kind of going for that sound.

author_blurb:
Original by Nine Inch Nails - Additional Production & ReMix by TweakerRay

This is another take on "Only". I have remixed this one in 2000 and this here is now the version I have done 15 years later.
I enjoy both versions. If you want to check out all nine inch nails remixes I have done, check out http://www.tweakerray.de/nineinchnailsremixes.html

If you want to support my work - Check out my original stuff at http://tweakerray.bandcamp.com or check out my mainpage: http://www.tweakerray.de

If you sign my newsletter there you get 26 Tracks for free of my music.

Cheers TweakerRay

author: D (The Distant)
title: Crushed2Death Mix
file: Nine Inch Nails - NINRemixes.com Official - 4199 - Me, I'm Not, Crushed2Death Mix, by D (The Distant).mp3
author_blurb:
Had so much fun playing with this song!
This is the first time I've ever remixed someone else's music & I can't wait to do it again...
Nine Inch Nails is probably the biggest inspiration for my band, The Distant & I do a lot of bit crushing in that music, so I guess you could say this is my homage to not only one of the best electronic rock albums ever made, but to the type of sounds that helped to mold my musical world...Hope you like it! Thanks     

D - The Distant
http://www.facebook.com/thedistantmusic
